(
<figureCitation id="71B52A0AFFE2FF83DB77F661F8DE4F06" box="[1634,1798,2543,2580]" captionStart="FIGURE 69" captionStartId="37.[840,931,2673,2703]" captionTargetBox="[527,1888,1841,2662]" captionText="FIGURE 69.—Approximate range of the gruti group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828584/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFE2FF83DB77F661F9154F06" bold="true" box="[1634,1741,2543,2580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">Figure</emphasis>
69
</figureCitation>
).—I 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFE2FF83DA4AF661F7D94F06" bold="true" box="[1887,2049,2543,2580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">have seen</emphasis>
six specimens from the following 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFE2FF83DBF5F593F8AA4F50" bold="true" box="[1760,1906,2589,2626]" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">localities</emphasis>
: SOUTH 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFE2FF83D876F5EFF9B74F6D" bold="true" box="[1379,1647,2657,2687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">AMERICA: BRAZIL</emphasis>
: Rio 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFE2FF83DBDDF5EFF9304F6D" bold="true" box="[1736,1768,2657,2687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">de</emphasis>
Janeiro Province: &quot; 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFE2FF83D51BF5EFF7994F6D" bold="true" box="[2062,2113,2657,2687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">Rio</emphasis>
Janeiro&quot; (BMNH); Rio Parahyba (MHNP). Santa Clara Province: Nova 
<taxonomicName id="2E8E4D0CFFE2FF83D8F2F521F9BE4FDF" box="[1511,1638,2735,2765]" class="Arachnida" family="Teutoniidae" genus="Teutonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Teutonia</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFE2FF83DB93F521F9164FDF" bold="true" box="[1670,1742,2735,2765]" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">MCZ</emphasis>
, USNM).
</paragraph>
